HEADWORD: Scopula
<hw>Scop"u*la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Scopulas</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Scopulae</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>scopulae</ets>, pl. a little
broom.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A peculiar brushlike
organ found on the foot of spiders and used in the construction of the
web.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A special tuft of hairs on the leg of a
bee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

